WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:15.432
[dramatic music playing]

3
00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:57.682
[music intensifies]

4
00:01:07.108 --> 00:01:09.110
[music fades]

5
00:01:15.617 --> 00:01:17.619
[ominous music playing]

6
00:01:21.456 --> 00:01:23.458
[flies buzzing]

7
00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:40.767
-[ominous music continues]
-[camera clicking]

8
00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:43.853
-[crowd chattering distantly]
-[car horns honking]

9
00:01:49.943 --> 00:01:52.862
Okay. this will work.

10
00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:56.991
-[music turns tense. hopeful]
-[Poe groaning]

11
00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.079
You're telling me this looked real?

12
00:02:01.162 --> 00:02:03.289
Yeah. I've seen the real thing.

13
00:02:04.165 --> 00:02:06.000
-This will work.
-[Poe sighs]

14
00:02:06.084 --> 00:02:07.168
[Poe] Can I see them?

15
00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:08.628
[Melo] No. Trust me.

16
00:02:08.711 --> 00:02:11.422
You don't want those images in your head.

17
00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.134
[Creasy] Yeah. these'll pass.

18
00:02:16.010 --> 00:02:17.262
Hey. you okay?

19
00:02:17.929 --> 00:02:20.557
Yeah. Let's get you your new clothes.
Come on.

20
00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:26.980
[sniffs. sighs]

21
00:02:29.774 --> 00:02:31.776
[music fades]

22
00:02:41.995 --> 00:02:43.997
Extraction team.

23
00:02:44.998 --> 00:02:45.957
Midnight.

24
00:02:46.916 --> 00:02:48.751
You've worked with this Tappen guy?

25
00:02:49.252 --> 00:02:50.920
Worked with him many times.

26
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:54.299
And you think he'll come through?

27
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:57.760
I think he'll do his best.

28
00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:03.183
Okay. I gotta go.

29
00:03:03.933 --> 00:03:07.353
Uh-- Oh. wait.
you cannot just leave me here.

30
00:03:07.437 --> 00:03:11.691
If there's an emergency. you can call.
but this is a safe place.

31
00:03:11.774 --> 00:03:13.568
You don't need me to babysit.
but get you home.

32
00:03:13.651 --> 00:03:16.029
Can we not just wait here
until it's time to go?

33
00:03:16.112 --> 00:03:18.656
I said Tappen's plan might be an option.
not a solution.

34
00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:22.452
Well. I didn't understand what that meant
the first time you said it either. so…

35
00:03:22.535 --> 00:03:24.078
[both sigh]

36
00:03:24.162 --> 00:03:26.080
Now. Poe…

37
00:03:26.164 --> 00:03:28.166
[poignant pensive music playing]

38
00:03:29.125 --> 00:03:30.585
We don't know

39
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:33.296
who attacked you at the base.

40
00:03:34.422 --> 00:03:38.051
Until I find that out
and eliminate that threat.

41
00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:39.594
you are not safe.

42
00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:42.513
You know. he…

43
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:49.270
He tried to teach me self-defense
so I could be safe.

44
00:03:51.898 --> 00:03:55.610
So I could know
what to do with my hands in case…

45
00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:57.612
[inhales sharply. sighs]

46
00:03:57.695 --> 00:03:59.405
That's good advice.

47
00:04:02.408 --> 00:04:04.994
Yeah. would be
if I bothered to remember any of it.

48
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:06.037
Hey.

49
00:04:07.914 --> 00:04:10.959
Doesn't matter what you can or can't do
with those hands.

50
00:04:13.044 --> 00:04:14.796
This one is in mine.

51
00:04:20.009 --> 00:04:21.302
[sighs]

52
00:04:22.553 --> 00:04:24.305
[music turns ominous]

53
00:04:24.389 --> 00:04:25.348
No. no. no.

54
00:04:25.431 --> 00:04:26.474
No.

55
00:04:26.557 --> 00:04:28.351
[music fades]

56
00:04:28.434 --> 00:04:30.395
No. No. No.

57
00:04:30.478 --> 00:04:32.397
No. no. [breathing heavily]

58
00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:34.607
I'm only gonna say this one time.

59
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:40.655
It's a bad idea to move around when
someone has a knife next to your heart.

60
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:45.410
[in Spanish] Tell me about Osmar.

61
00:04:45.910 --> 00:04:48.496
[Tiago groaning]

62
00:04:49.622 --> 00:04:51.165
I already told you.

63
00:04:52.333 --> 00:04:54.210
Osmar is some kind of code name.

64
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.172
He hired us to help hit your convoy.

65
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:01.467
I never met him or anyone with him before.

66
00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:05.430
I'm asking. what does he look like?

67
00:05:07.181 --> 00:05:09.267
Well… [breathing heavily]

68
00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:10.518
Tall.

69
00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:11.894
Gray hair.

70
00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:14.939
Big scar down the left side of his face.

71
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.025
[Tiago groans]

72
00:05:20.069 --> 00:05:21.446
[exhales shakily]

73
00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:24.532
[Tiago groans]

74
00:05:24.615 --> 00:05:26.284
When we get there.

75
00:05:27.201 --> 00:05:28.995
how do we contact him?

76
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:31.039
[Tiago gasps]

77
00:05:32.790 --> 00:05:36.461
A call box on the front of the building
that's been rigged to call Osmar.

78
00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:40.631
From there he will tell you where to meet.

79
00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:43.426
[groaning]

80
00:05:43.509 --> 00:05:44.635
What have you done to me?

81
00:05:44.719 --> 00:05:46.888
[Tiago breathing heavily]

82
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:50.850
[in English] Put a little
homemade blasting cap

83
00:05:51.934 --> 00:05:52.894
in your chest.

84
00:05:52.977 --> 00:05:54.687
What?! [whimpers]

85
00:05:54.771 --> 00:05:58.399
[in Spanish] There is a device
in your chest.

86
00:06:00.526 --> 00:06:02.528
I press this button…

87
00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:05.531
and boom.

88
00:06:05.615 --> 00:06:06.824
[gasps]

89
00:06:06.908 --> 00:06:10.620
You are a very sick person.
Do you know that?

90
00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:18.294
Which one of us
was about to shoot a teenage girl?

91
00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.380
[ominous music playing]

92
00:06:21.297 --> 00:06:23.007
For people like me.

93
00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:28.179
there are necessary evils
to survive the world we live in.

94
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:30.431
But you.

95
00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:31.766
asshole.

96
00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:34.769
you come from a land of luxury.

97
00:06:35.561 --> 00:06:39.107
You <i>chose </i>this job. this way of living.

98
00:06:40.441 --> 00:06:42.902
Whatever you've told yourself

99
00:06:42.985 --> 00:06:46.280
about why you've entered this
or what you were before. that's all gone.

100
00:06:46.864 --> 00:06:49.784
But if there's a difference
between you and me.

101
00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:53.830
it's that you are far worse.
son of a bitch.

102
00:06:57.792 --> 00:07:00.002
[in English] Then you should
probably keep in mind

103
00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:03.297
which one of us is holding the remote.

104
00:07:05.216 --> 00:07:06.843
[man in Portuguese] Do you trust this man?

105
00:07:07.510 --> 00:07:08.803
I trust him.

106
00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:12.515
He works at a security company.
Something went down.

107
00:07:12.598 --> 00:07:13.808
What went down?

108
00:07:14.684 --> 00:07:17.770
Guys tried to hold him up.
He took them apart like it was nothing.

109
00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:18.980
He must be crazy.

110
00:07:19.063 --> 00:07:21.858
He's CIA. or Special Forces. I don't know.

111
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:25.319
-Mm-hmm.
-The money is coming from the Americans.

112
00:07:25.403 --> 00:07:26.696
It's going to show up.

113
00:07:27.196 --> 00:07:30.616
-[indistinct chatter]
-[Portuguese rap music playing distantly]

114
00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:32.702
[car horns honking]

115
00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:39.000
[in English] Mr. Creasy.
This is Beto. my husband's cousin.

116
00:07:39.083 --> 00:07:40.209
Hi.

117
00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:41.878
I need to get back to my daughter.

118
00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:44.380
He's going to make sure Poe is safe
while you're away.

119
00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:48.301
Look. man. she's in good hands.

120
00:07:48.885 --> 00:07:51.929
When I get back. I'll have enough money
to make everybody whole.

121
00:07:52.013 --> 00:07:53.306
[in Portuguese] We'll talk later.

122
00:07:58.269 --> 00:08:00.688
[in English] This is not
just about getting the money. right?

123
00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:05.985
That guy you brought here.
He's going with you?

124
00:08:06.068 --> 00:08:07.111
Yeah.

125
00:08:07.945 --> 00:08:09.113
Is he coming back?

126
00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:11.741
It's up to him.

127
00:08:16.996 --> 00:08:18.998
[Portuguese rap music continues]

128
00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:24.545
[Portuguese rap music
continues over stereo]

129
00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:28.424
[Beto in Portuguese]
Melo is my family. right. bro?

130
00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:30.468
What the hell?

131
00:08:31.969 --> 00:08:33.638
This is my job. man.

132
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:38.226
I don't need any help.

133
00:08:38.309 --> 00:08:39.936
How will you handle security

134
00:08:40.019 --> 00:08:42.897
when you're going on a run
with half your guys?

135
00:08:43.856 --> 00:08:45.483
I'll put Livro with her.

136
00:08:45.566 --> 00:08:48.110
-[laughs] Livro? Your baby brother?
-[laughing]

137
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.737
Are you fucking kidding me?

138
00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:54.367
You'd be better off giving the girl a gun
and asking her to defend him.

139
00:08:56.077 --> 00:08:57.328
Duda.

140
00:08:57.411 --> 00:08:58.538
all I'm saying is.

141
00:08:58.621 --> 00:09:01.415
if we're going to do this.
let's do it right.

142
00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:04.168
Me and my guys
will provide the proper protection

143
00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:06.671
and in exchange I'm just asking for a cut.

144
00:09:06.754 --> 00:09:08.589
I've already had my say. brother.

145
00:09:09.131 --> 00:09:10.800
I don't need them.

146
00:09:11.884 --> 00:09:14.136
I don't need them and I don't want them.

147
00:09:15.721 --> 00:09:17.557
Livro speaks English so fucking well.

148
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.309
He'll make her feel calm
and keep her out of the way.

149
00:09:21.602 --> 00:09:25.273
Besides. it's about time he finds a way
to start pulling his fucking weight.

150
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:29.402
It's his find.

151
00:09:29.485 --> 00:09:31.571
He can do it his way.

152
00:09:31.654 --> 00:09:34.198
If he wants to use it
to help bring his brother along…

153
00:09:35.950 --> 00:09:37.326
that's his business.

154
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.996
When this turns into a mess
and someone has to step in?

155
00:09:40.079 --> 00:09:42.039
It's not gonna turn into anything.

156
00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:44.208
It's handled.

157
00:09:47.211 --> 00:09:48.546
We'll see about that.

158
00:09:48.629 --> 00:09:50.631
[Portuguese rap music continues]

159
00:09:55.386 --> 00:09:56.387
[music fades]

160
00:09:56.470 --> 00:09:59.932
I don't understand.
Why do I have to keep an eye on this girl?

161
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.225
I told you!

162
00:10:01.726 --> 00:10:04.020
You don't do a fucking thing
around here. Livro.

163
00:10:04.103 --> 00:10:06.522
There are kids younger than you on a crew.

164
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:08.316
Earning. you know?

165
00:10:08.399 --> 00:10:10.067
[crew members chattering indistinctly]

166
00:10:10.151 --> 00:10:12.403
It's time to fucking man up.

167
00:10:12.903 --> 00:10:13.946
It's real simple.

168
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:15.823
You won't do anything.

169
00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:18.075
You don't do anything anyway. right?

170
00:10:18.784 --> 00:10:20.953
Stay inside the shack
with the girl. understand?

171
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:24.582
And whatever you do.
stay the fuck away from Vico.

172
00:10:25.082 --> 00:10:26.459
I'll hook you up.

173
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.838
-Don't get used to it.
-You're crazy. I'm just watching her.

174
00:10:30.921 --> 00:10:33.090
[scoffs] Jesus fucking Christ.

175
00:10:33.174 --> 00:10:34.759
I don't want that.

176
00:10:35.551 --> 00:10:37.762
I'm trying to help you. Livro.

177
00:10:38.262 --> 00:10:40.806
You're the only one
who doesn't fucking carry.

178
00:10:42.975 --> 00:10:44.060
[Livro] Are you crazy?

179
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:47.021
Anyone who looks at you
can see you're weak. damn it.

180
00:10:47.104 --> 00:10:48.439
Are you weak?

181
00:10:48.522 --> 00:10:50.816
You're not weak. You're my brother.

182
00:10:51.317 --> 00:10:53.611
From today on
you're going to be armed. damn it.

183
00:10:54.111 --> 00:10:55.821
You start earning.

184
00:10:58.699 --> 00:11:00.117
Are you crying?

185
00:11:01.243 --> 00:11:02.161
[Livro sniffles]

186
00:11:02.244 --> 00:11:06.582
If you cry here. kid.
I'll kill you myself.

187
00:11:08.709 --> 00:11:10.127
Now toughen up.

188
00:11:12.046 --> 00:11:13.339
Come on.

189
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:17.760
Go out there and show
you're a loose animal in this shithole.

190
00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:19.428
Go!

191
00:11:26.977 --> 00:11:28.396
[sighs]

192
00:11:31.607 --> 00:11:33.609
[poignant pensive music playing]

193
00:11:59.468 --> 00:12:01.178
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

194
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:05.266
[music fades]

195
00:12:08.144 --> 00:12:10.104
-[gasps]
-[in English] Oh. I'm-- I'm sorry.

196
00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:13.607
I didn't mean to scare you.

197
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:17.570
I was asked to see after you for the day.

198
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:20.156
I'm Livro.

199
00:12:26.787 --> 00:12:29.457
I don't need anybody to look after me.

200
00:12:29.540 --> 00:12:32.418
So. can you leave. please?

201
00:12:34.879 --> 00:12:35.921
I apologize again.

202
00:12:37.339 --> 00:12:40.217
Um. I'll sit outside. near the door.

203
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:42.678
You won't even notice I'm here.

204
00:12:44.346 --> 00:12:46.098
How do you speak English so well?

205
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:53.022
I've had some lessons. but the Internet
and American television help very much.

206
00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:54.023
[chuckles softly]

207
00:12:54.857 --> 00:12:57.568
Um. sorry. your name is "Book"?

208
00:12:58.444 --> 00:12:59.945
Yeah. it's…

209
00:13:00.029 --> 00:13:01.322
Livro.

210
00:13:02.031 --> 00:13:04.408
Everyone goes by a nickname here.

211
00:13:04.492 --> 00:13:05.659
So.

212
00:13:05.743 --> 00:13:08.162
you do things like this all the time?

213
00:13:09.872 --> 00:13:11.081
No.

214
00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:15.252
My brother asked me to.

215
00:13:15.336 --> 00:13:21.675
You see. when I was very young.
our parents were killed.

216
00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:25.262
So my brother needed to take care of us.

217
00:13:27.306 --> 00:13:31.101
But now he's on the lookout
for jobs he thinks I can do.

218
00:13:31.185 --> 00:13:34.063
And… I guess this was one of them.

219
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:36.524
So you didn't want to do it?

220
00:13:38.359 --> 00:13:39.860
No. I…

221
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:43.447
He always looked out for me. you know?

222
00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:48.369
But now he's realizing
that I'm just not like him. And…

223
00:13:49.954 --> 00:13:52.414
I think he started to hate me for it.

224
00:13:55.376 --> 00:13:57.586
[inhales deeply] Um…

225
00:13:57.670 --> 00:14:00.506
Would you like to watch something on TV?

226
00:14:02.466 --> 00:14:03.676
Is it in English?

227
00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:08.055
Oh. on there. probably no.

228
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:11.976
But you can watch on my phone.

229
00:14:12.476 --> 00:14:13.435
Here.

230
00:14:16.397 --> 00:14:17.481
[sniffles softly]

231
00:14:18.649 --> 00:14:21.235
You can watch with me. if you want.

232
00:14:22.027 --> 00:14:22.987
Okay.

233
00:14:25.406 --> 00:14:26.907
Do you miss your parents?

234
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:28.993
[poignant pensive music playing]

235
00:14:31.161 --> 00:14:32.288
Very much.

236
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:38.711
-Oh. I'm sorry.
-No.

237
00:14:39.545 --> 00:14:40.838
No. um.

238
00:14:41.714 --> 00:14:42.965
it's okay. I…

239
00:14:43.465 --> 00:14:48.012
I worry more about forgetting
than not being able to.

240
00:14:49.930 --> 00:14:51.307
Trust me.

241
00:14:52.766 --> 00:14:54.435
You never forget.

242
00:14:57.062 --> 00:14:59.481
[Portuguese rap music playing]

243
00:15:23.255 --> 00:15:25.257
[music fades]

244
00:15:33.098 --> 00:15:34.224
Don't be stupid.

245
00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:36.310
[breathing heavily]

246
00:15:39.855 --> 00:15:41.982
[Creasy] I'm gonna step away from the car.

247
00:15:43.317 --> 00:15:45.277
But I still have my eye on it.

248
00:15:45.903 --> 00:15:47.196
[coughs]

249
00:15:52.618 --> 00:15:56.914
If you think about messing around.
remember you're very much still in range.

250
00:15:58.082 --> 00:16:01.168
[in Portuguese] Don't need to leave me
roasting here. dude. Come on…

251
00:16:01.251 --> 00:16:03.754
[ominous music playing]

252
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:12.721
[cell phone beeps]

253
00:16:12.805 --> 00:16:15.057
[line dialing]

254
00:16:17.017 --> 00:16:17.935
[cell phone beeps]

255
00:16:19.144 --> 00:16:21.063
[man in English]
<i>Money's at the bottom of the bag.</i>

256
00:16:21.146 --> 00:16:23.399
<i>They told me the extraction</i>
<i>was set for midnight.</i>

257
00:16:23.482 --> 00:16:25.484
[tourists speaking indistinctly]

258
00:16:25.567 --> 00:16:27.736
[Creasy] <i>What can you tell me</i>
<i>about the FRP?</i>

259
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:29.405
The FRP has made trouble for Carmo.

260
00:16:29.488 --> 00:16:31.907
mostly small actions
hoping to swing the election.

261
00:16:31.991 --> 00:16:33.242
<i>But all they really accomplished</i>

262
00:16:33.325 --> 00:16:35.619
<i>is getting their leader. Ferraz.</i>
<i>thrown in jail.</i>

263
00:16:37.287 --> 00:16:41.333
<i>I guess whoever replaced him has decided</i>
<i>to respond by blowing up a building.</i>

264
00:16:41.417 --> 00:16:43.752
That's a pretty large job
for somebody new to terrorism.

265
00:16:43.836 --> 00:16:45.170
They have anybody with a history?

266
00:16:45.254 --> 00:16:46.547
Hard to say.

267
00:16:46.630 --> 00:16:49.508
They don't cover them directly.
but I know they're organized in cells.

268
00:16:49.591 --> 00:16:51.635
so the damage from a crackdown is limited.

269
00:16:51.719 --> 00:16:53.804
<i>Outside of the actual bombers.</i>

270
00:16:53.887 --> 00:16:55.848
<i>I doubt most members</i>
<i>would know anything about it</i>

271
00:16:55.931 --> 00:16:57.307
<i>until it actually happened.</i>

272
00:16:57.391 --> 00:17:00.185
What about a guy named Osmar?
He might have a scar on his face.

273
00:17:00.811 --> 00:17:02.354
Don't know of anyone like that.

274
00:17:02.438 --> 00:17:04.481
<i>These don't sound</i>
<i>like the questions of someone</i>

275
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:06.483
<i>who's planning to leave at midnight.</i>

276
00:17:07.693 --> 00:17:12.489
Nah. I'm just… making sure
people reap what they sow.

277
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:14.575
[ominous music continues]

278
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:19.038
[music fades]

279
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:25.461
-[siren wailing distantly]
-[car horns honking]

280
00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:32.426
[man yelling indistinctly]

281
00:17:36.221 --> 00:17:37.181
[intercom beeps]

282
00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:39.099
[man in Portuguese] <i>Yes.</i>

283
00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:40.601
It's Tiago.

284
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:42.436
<i>Tiago?</i>

285
00:17:43.020 --> 00:17:44.813
<i>Your people thought you didn't make it.</i>

286
00:17:45.814 --> 00:17:48.025
<i>It was more than I bargained for.</i>

287
00:17:48.525 --> 00:17:51.653
<i>but I got the job done</i>
<i>and ended with a hell of a story.</i>

288
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:54.865
What I need now is to be paid as agreed.

289
00:17:54.948 --> 00:17:56.200
<i>Wait. wait. wait.</i>

290
00:17:56.283 --> 00:18:00.079
<i>What do you mean you finished the job?</i>
<i>The word is they got away.</i>

291
00:18:01.371 --> 00:18:03.040
They did.

292
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:04.917
<i>But I went with them.</i>

293
00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:05.959
[man] Well. well.

294
00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:07.878
That's very good work. Tiago.

295
00:18:08.962 --> 00:18:10.172
<i>Do it like this.</i>

296
00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:12.299
<i>Go to the store at the end of the block.</i>

297
00:18:12.382 --> 00:18:14.927
<i>There's a rack of pre-paid cell phones.</i>

298
00:18:15.511 --> 00:18:17.429
<i>Buy the one in the back on the left.</i>

299
00:18:18.388 --> 00:18:20.099
I'll call within the hour.

300
00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:21.892
When we have your money.

301
00:18:26.230 --> 00:18:27.773
What are you doing?

302
00:18:28.273 --> 00:18:30.192
He gave us instructions.

303
00:18:30.275 --> 00:18:33.987
A phone in the back left of a store
down the street.

304
00:18:34.071 --> 00:18:36.532
And then he will call to arrange.

305
00:18:37.116 --> 00:18:38.033
Understand?

306
00:18:38.534 --> 00:18:40.828
[in English] No.
We're not gonna do it like that.

307
00:18:40.911 --> 00:18:43.872
We're gonna see him right now. Now walk.

308
00:18:49.294 --> 00:18:51.755
[ominous music playing]

309
00:19:18.365 --> 00:19:20.367
[music intensifies]

310
00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:22.536
[man speaking indistinctly]

311
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:30.043
[men chattering indistinctly]

312
00:19:32.421 --> 00:19:34.006
[music turns dramatic]

313
00:19:34.089 --> 00:19:35.382
-[remote beeps]
-[explosion]

314
00:19:35.465 --> 00:19:36.383
[music fades]

315
00:19:36.466 --> 00:19:37.926
[men speaking in Portuguese]

316
00:19:38.594 --> 00:19:40.095
[intense music playing]

317
00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:41.471
[body thuds]

318
00:19:44.516 --> 00:19:45.392
[in English] Fuck.

319
00:19:45.475 --> 00:19:47.144
[men yelling in Portuguese]

320
00:19:52.316 --> 00:19:54.067
[man 1] This way.

321
00:19:59.239 --> 00:20:00.324
[man 2] Go. go. go.

322
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:03.827
-[music turns suspenseful]
-[men yelling indistinctly]

323
00:20:13.712 --> 00:20:14.922
[man 2] Go. go.

324
00:20:17.758 --> 00:20:19.927
-[grunting]
-[music turns intense]

325
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:24.264
[Creasy grunts]

326
00:20:25.349 --> 00:20:26.934
[man grunting]

327
00:20:30.687 --> 00:20:31.897
-[man grunts]
-[metal pierces]

328
00:20:34.107 --> 00:20:35.025
[groans]

329
00:20:35.567 --> 00:20:37.736
[tense music playing]

330
00:20:52.376 --> 00:20:53.210
[in English] Fuck.

331
00:20:53.293 --> 00:20:54.503
[music fades]

332
00:20:54.586 --> 00:20:56.546
[Poe] Look. I haven't had
anything to eat in hours.

333
00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:58.840
And I'm kind of sick
of being in this room.

334
00:20:58.924 --> 00:21:02.010
And I'm just asking to get out of here
for like five minutes.

335
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.095
Okay.

336
00:21:03.595 --> 00:21:06.556
Okay. but we must go and come right back.

337
00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:08.976
-Five minutes.
-Like five minutes. yeah.

338
00:21:12.020 --> 00:21:13.105
[Poe clears throat]

339
00:21:15.899 --> 00:21:17.901
[indistinct chatter]

340
00:21:18.944 --> 00:21:20.487
It's just down there.

341
00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:24.658
Oh my God.

342
00:21:27.035 --> 00:21:29.413
[dramatic pensive music playing]

343
00:21:30.289 --> 00:21:31.832
[Livro] It's beautiful. no?

344
00:21:33.083 --> 00:21:34.418
[Poe] Yeah. I mean…

345
00:21:35.127 --> 00:21:37.838
It's the best thing I've seen
since I got to Brazil.

346
00:21:38.422 --> 00:21:39.673
Look down there.

347
00:21:40.299 --> 00:21:43.719
This is the only city I know
where the poor live above the rich.

348
00:21:45.304 --> 00:21:48.932
Um. we should go.
Our five minutes are disappearing.

349
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:55.314
[dramatic pensive music continues]

350
00:22:03.947 --> 00:22:05.949
[music swells]

351
00:22:06.033 --> 00:22:09.036
-[music fades]
-[man speaking in Portuguese on radio]

352
00:22:09.119 --> 00:22:11.121
[crowd chattering indistinctly]

353
00:22:12.622 --> 00:22:16.209
It's not what I thought it would be.
It's actually kind of pretty.

354
00:22:16.293 --> 00:22:19.087
Oh. you were expecting…

355
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:20.505
What is the word?

356
00:22:20.589 --> 00:22:22.257
Uh. slum. right?

357
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:24.509
No. No. sorry--
I-- I didn't mean to offend you.

358
00:22:24.593 --> 00:22:26.803
No. it's okay. It's okay.

359
00:22:26.887 --> 00:22:30.182
-This is what everyone thinks.
-[man and woman speaking indistinctly]

360
00:22:30.265 --> 00:22:32.434
And then it's fun to see them surprised.

361
00:22:32.517 --> 00:22:33.352
[laughs softly]

362
00:22:36.021 --> 00:22:37.689
Do you like to read?

363
00:22:38.857 --> 00:22:40.400
Yeah. why?

364
00:22:41.693 --> 00:22:45.030
Very quickly.
I'll show you my favorite place.

365
00:22:48.033 --> 00:22:50.035
[subtle ominous music playing]

366
00:22:56.500 --> 00:22:57.501
[music fades]

367
00:22:58.085 --> 00:23:01.171
My grandmother used to bring me here
when I first arrived.

368
00:23:02.798 --> 00:23:03.840
[chuckles]

369
00:23:04.716 --> 00:23:05.967
I spent so many times here

370
00:23:06.051 --> 00:23:09.930
that they let me
sit behind the counter and read. you know?

371
00:23:10.430 --> 00:23:13.266
And there isn't much competition
for the ones in English.

372
00:23:13.350 --> 00:23:16.728
so I often find good choices.

373
00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:20.816
Something you like?

374
00:23:24.236 --> 00:23:26.613
{\an8}Oh. you are a chess player.

375
00:23:27.155 --> 00:23:28.615
No.

376
00:23:28.698 --> 00:23:29.574
Um…

377
00:23:29.658 --> 00:23:32.160
But my dad used to play and

378
00:23:33.286 --> 00:23:34.871
I remember this book.

379
00:23:37.582 --> 00:23:40.585
-[children chattering indistinctly]
-[ominous music playing]

380
00:23:47.342 --> 00:23:48.552
-I. uh…
-We must go.

381
00:23:48.635 --> 00:23:52.139
[in Portuguese] Well. well. well.
If it isn't Livro The Bodyguard.

382
00:23:52.222 --> 00:23:54.975
Watch out. guys.
Elite-level protection endorsed by Beto.

383
00:23:55.058 --> 00:23:56.601
-[laughs]
-We're already leaving.

384
00:23:56.685 --> 00:23:57.727
Oh! Oh! Oh!

385
00:23:57.811 --> 00:23:59.729
But we just arrived. [laughs]

386
00:23:59.813 --> 00:24:01.731
[Poe gasps. whimpers]

387
00:24:02.274 --> 00:24:04.734
-[groaning]
-[tense music playing]

388
00:24:04.818 --> 00:24:06.611
Oh. is this a problem for you?

389
00:24:07.195 --> 00:24:09.781
Because Beto seemed to think
you could handle this.

390
00:24:09.865 --> 00:24:12.117
-Vico…
-[Vico] So I want to see you handle it.

391
00:24:12.200 --> 00:24:13.994
[yells] Livro!

392
00:24:14.077 --> 00:24:15.495
Vico. please!

393
00:24:16.413 --> 00:24:18.498
-Please?
-[gasps]

394
00:24:18.582 --> 00:24:20.250
[gang members laughing]

395
00:24:20.834 --> 00:24:24.254
I got a knife to her throat.
and he says please!

396
00:24:24.337 --> 00:24:25.172
[Poe] Livro!

397
00:24:25.255 --> 00:24:26.882
[tense music continues]

398
00:24:27.799 --> 00:24:30.677
[laughing] Her bodyguard is packing.

399
00:24:32.929 --> 00:24:36.099
I don't want you to hit
the person you're protecting.

400
00:24:36.183 --> 00:24:37.434
[Poe gasping]

401
00:24:39.561 --> 00:24:40.770
See.

402
00:24:41.771 --> 00:24:43.231
for this to work.

403
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:49.029
I have to be more afraid of dying
than you are of shooting. [laughing]

404
00:24:50.447 --> 00:24:52.949
-[grunts. coughs]
-[gang member laughs]

405
00:24:53.783 --> 00:24:55.202
[Livro gasping]

406
00:24:56.661 --> 00:24:57.704
[Vico laughs]

407
00:24:57.787 --> 00:24:59.247
You're not cut out for this.

408
00:25:00.123 --> 00:25:01.458
You know that?

409
00:25:06.588 --> 00:25:08.423
You think I'm an asshole. don't you?

410
00:25:09.007 --> 00:25:11.092
It's okay. Livro. I am an asshole.

411
00:25:11.676 --> 00:25:13.386
So what you have to ask yourself

412
00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:16.348
is why an asshole's more concerned
about you in these situations

413
00:25:16.431 --> 00:25:17.891
than your own brother?

414
00:25:19.267 --> 00:25:21.478
I'm not nearly as smart as you.

415
00:25:22.521 --> 00:25:26.316
but I think if an asshole
is the only one looking out for you.

416
00:25:26.399 --> 00:25:28.360
you've got a problem.

417
00:25:28.443 --> 00:25:29.778
[shudders]

418
00:25:31.404 --> 00:25:33.240
[gasping]

419
00:25:35.325 --> 00:25:36.993
[music fades]

420
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:39.663
[dramatic music playing]

421
00:25:47.212 --> 00:25:49.172
Take it from an asshole. Livro.

422
00:25:49.923 --> 00:25:53.635
If you're not one.
you don't want to become one.

423
00:26:00.600 --> 00:26:01.434
[Poe gasps]

424
00:26:01.518 --> 00:26:02.352
Let's go.

425
00:26:07.065 --> 00:26:09.067
[dramatic music continues]

426
00:26:18.243 --> 00:26:20.245
[music fades]

427
00:26:20.328 --> 00:26:23.331
[Portuguese rap music playing over radio]

428
00:26:31.923 --> 00:26:32.841
[in Spanish] Just this.

429
00:26:32.924 --> 00:26:35.093
[cell phone buzzing]

430
00:26:38.138 --> 00:26:39.472
[in English] Hey. Poe?

431
00:26:40.140 --> 00:26:42.017
-[Poe] <i>He attacked us.</i>
-What? Who?

432
00:26:42.100 --> 00:26:43.310
[tense music playing]

433
00:26:43.393 --> 00:26:45.604
<i>-Who?</i>
-I don't know. Uh…

434
00:26:47.939 --> 00:26:49.399
A rival gang or something.

435
00:26:51.318 --> 00:26:55.071
<i>-Creasy. you've gotta come back. Please.</i>
-[Creasy] You okay? Where are you now?

436
00:26:56.114 --> 00:26:57.449
I'm at the apartment.

437
00:27:00.702 --> 00:27:03.038
-What do they want?
<i>-I don't know.</i>

438
00:27:03.121 --> 00:27:05.665
<i>Uh. I think they were</i>
<i>just trying to scare us.</i>

439
00:27:05.749 --> 00:27:08.168
But-- [sniffles] When can you be here?

440
00:27:08.251 --> 00:27:09.461
-I-- It…
-[cell phone ringing]

441
00:27:09.544 --> 00:27:11.254
<i>Aren't we supposed to be leaving?</i>

442
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:13.548
<i>The plane was supposed to take us home.</i>

443
00:27:13.632 --> 00:27:16.217
[ominous music playing]

444
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:17.344
Creasy?

445
00:27:18.178 --> 00:27:20.347
-<i>Creasy?</i>
-[cell phone continues ringing]

446
00:27:20.430 --> 00:27:22.015
I gotta go. I'll be back in a second.

447
00:27:22.098 --> 00:27:23.850
-Stay inside. Lock the door.
<i>-I--</i>

448
00:27:23.933 --> 00:27:25.560
[call disconnects]

449
00:27:26.269 --> 00:27:28.271
[cell phone continues ringing]

450
00:27:32.400 --> 00:27:33.276
Yeah?

451
00:27:33.360 --> 00:27:35.445
[man] <i>Who are you? What do you want?</i>

452
00:27:35.528 --> 00:27:37.447
I think you already know who this is.

453
00:27:38.198 --> 00:27:41.034
But if you want to be sure.
tell me where to meet you.

454
00:27:41.117 --> 00:27:43.411
-I'll be happy to fill you in.
<i>-It's okay.</i>

455
00:27:43.495 --> 00:27:45.955
<i>We enjoy watching you</i>
<i>sit in your little car.</i>

456
00:27:46.039 --> 00:27:48.041
[tense music playing]

457
00:27:51.252 --> 00:27:52.337
[engine starts]

458
00:27:54.631 --> 00:27:56.800
[radio interference crackling softly]

459
00:27:56.883 --> 00:27:58.802
[man speaking indistinctly over radio]

460
00:28:02.055 --> 00:28:04.057
[tense pensive music playing]

461
00:28:07.060 --> 00:28:09.104
[crackling increases. fades]

462
00:28:09.187 --> 00:28:11.356
[crackling increases. fades]

463
00:28:18.905 --> 00:28:21.199
[crackling increases]

464
00:28:22.242 --> 00:28:23.618
Okay. then.

465
00:28:39.926 --> 00:28:41.928
[dramatic music playing]

466
00:29:00.196 --> 00:29:04.826
ROTARY AND MONTHLY PARKING

467
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:25.805
[dramatic music continues]

468
00:29:35.315 --> 00:29:36.691
Motherfucker.

469
00:29:42.781 --> 00:29:44.783
[music fades]

470
00:29:44.866 --> 00:29:46.117
EXPLOSION CAUSES TRAGEDY

471
00:29:46.201 --> 00:29:47.786
[man speaking in Portuguese on TV]

472
00:29:47.869 --> 00:29:49.245
[in Portuguese] Hi.

473
00:29:49.746 --> 00:29:50.789
Mom.

474
00:29:50.872 --> 00:29:52.916
-Where have you been?
-[Melo] I know. I'm sorry.

475
00:29:52.999 --> 00:29:53.875
You disappeared.

476
00:29:53.958 --> 00:29:56.002
I got a customer
who required my attention.

477
00:29:56.085 --> 00:29:57.504
You said you'd check in.

478
00:29:57.587 --> 00:29:59.297
I didn't have my phone.

479
00:30:01.216 --> 00:30:03.384
-Everything okay?
-Yeah. everything's okay.

480
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:05.512
-I wanted to talk to you.
-Of course.

481
00:30:05.595 --> 00:30:07.722
Before I left. I wanted to apologize.

482
00:30:07.806 --> 00:30:10.433
I went too far.
You don't want to leave. not my business.

483
00:30:10.517 --> 00:30:14.187
-I just want what's best for you two.
-I know. Gabi. Thanks.

484
00:30:15.522 --> 00:30:19.359
It's never been that I'm unwilling to go.
But I want to do it the right way.

485
00:30:19.442 --> 00:30:21.569
[pop music playing indistinctly
over headphones]

486
00:30:21.653 --> 00:30:23.655
I don't want Marina to be undocumented.

487
00:30:25.281 --> 00:30:27.033
And I think I've found a way.

488
00:30:27.534 --> 00:30:28.743
How?

489
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:30.578
-This passenger I'm working with now.
-Mm-hmm?

490
00:30:30.662 --> 00:30:32.789
He has connections.
He can help with the papers.

491
00:30:32.872 --> 00:30:34.374
But first I must help him.

492
00:30:34.457 --> 00:30:35.416
With what?

493
00:30:36.543 --> 00:30:38.461
He's after the people who did this.

494
00:30:38.545 --> 00:30:40.797
[ominous music playing]

495
00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:42.048
What?

496
00:30:42.549 --> 00:30:45.426
No. You don't want
to get mixed up in that.

497
00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:46.511
Who is he?

498
00:30:46.594 --> 00:30:49.889
The security contractors I'm driving for.
he's one of them.

499
00:30:50.390 --> 00:30:51.558
And you trust him?

500
00:30:52.725 --> 00:30:53.643
But why?

501
00:30:54.477 --> 00:30:55.895
I don't know.

502
00:30:55.979 --> 00:30:58.439
Sometimes you meet someone…

503
00:30:58.523 --> 00:31:00.358
It's like you see
a piece of yourself in them.

504
00:31:00.441 --> 00:31:02.652
And what part of yourself do you see?

505
00:31:03.236 --> 00:31:04.362
[laughs sadly]

506
00:31:05.321 --> 00:31:06.865
The part that's suffered.

507
00:31:07.991 --> 00:31:09.993
[music turns poignant]

508
00:31:15.999 --> 00:31:18.001
-[car tires screech]
-[engine revving]

509
00:31:19.752 --> 00:31:20.670
[brakes screech]

510
00:31:20.753 --> 00:31:22.672
[tense music playing]

511
00:31:22.755 --> 00:31:24.632
[man 1 in Portuguese] All good.

512
00:31:24.716 --> 00:31:26.175
Sweep the perimeter.

513
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:27.719
Make sure it's all secured.

514
00:31:29.345 --> 00:31:30.805
[man 2] This way. This way.

515
00:31:30.889 --> 00:31:32.056
[man 3] Watch out. Watch out.

516
00:31:32.140 --> 00:31:35.101
[man 2] This way.
Look under the car. under the car.

517
00:31:35.184 --> 00:31:37.312
[man 1] Hand on the gun. Visual. Fire.

518
00:31:37.395 --> 00:31:38.688
[man 2] Nothing here.

519
00:31:39.188 --> 00:31:41.190
[tense music continues]

520
00:31:49.324 --> 00:31:50.158
Fuck.

521
00:31:50.909 --> 00:31:52.911
[cell phone buzzing]

522
00:31:55.413 --> 00:31:56.372
[cell phone beeps]

523
00:31:57.165 --> 00:31:59.959
[Ferraz in English] <i>It's been hours</i>
<i>since he came to the warehouse.</i>

524
00:32:01.711 --> 00:32:03.046
<i>Do you have him?</i>

525
00:32:03.963 --> 00:32:05.089
No.

526
00:32:05.590 --> 00:32:08.343
He discovered the tracker. Threw it out.

527
00:32:08.426 --> 00:32:10.803
<i>Why didn't you take him</i>
<i>when you had the chance?</i>

528
00:32:10.887 --> 00:32:13.014
Because we need the girl as well.

529
00:32:13.097 --> 00:32:15.558
Having him lead us to her
would have allowed us to--

530
00:32:15.642 --> 00:32:20.104
<i>Consider yourself relieved.</i>
<i>I'll put the job in more competent hands.</i>

531
00:32:20.188 --> 00:32:21.272
Yes.

532
00:32:23.524 --> 00:32:24.901
Very well.

533
00:32:25.443 --> 00:32:27.820
-[breathes shakily]
-[call disconnects]

534
00:32:27.904 --> 00:32:29.906
[tense music continues]

535
00:32:39.457 --> 00:32:41.334
[in Portuguese]
I have been relieved of command.

536
00:32:42.043 --> 00:32:44.462
They will find a different way
to pursue them.

537
00:32:45.630 --> 00:32:48.925
If they need more.
someone else will contact you.

538
00:32:49.008 --> 00:32:52.887
Our guy in the store said
he dropped it when he got the phone.

539
00:32:54.597 --> 00:32:58.685
Have a couple guys stake out her place.
See if it goes anywhere.

540
00:32:59.185 --> 00:33:00.770
I'll be at home.

541
00:33:01.354 --> 00:33:02.897
[SUV engine starts]

542
00:33:09.487 --> 00:33:11.572
-[engine revs]
-[tires screech]

543
00:33:16.369 --> 00:33:18.371
[music fades]

544
00:33:18.454 --> 00:33:20.581
[Portuguese rap music playing distantly]

545
00:33:20.665 --> 00:33:21.958
[keypad clicking]

546
00:33:22.041 --> 00:33:24.043
[line dialing]

547
00:33:51.904 --> 00:33:52.864
[door opens]

548
00:33:58.619 --> 00:34:00.163
[in English] Still no word?

549
00:34:05.084 --> 00:34:06.294
What is that?

550
00:34:07.670 --> 00:34:10.423
I just wanted to bring you something
before you leave.

551
00:34:25.104 --> 00:34:30.902
The fact that you would find something
here that reminded you

552
00:34:31.402 --> 00:34:32.320
of home…

553
00:34:33.946 --> 00:34:36.074
I don't know. It seemed like fate.

554
00:34:36.157 --> 00:34:38.493
[poignant music playing]

555
00:34:38.576 --> 00:34:39.827
[softly] Thank you.

556
00:34:42.455 --> 00:34:43.915
I really appreciate it.

557
00:34:47.085 --> 00:34:49.045
And I'm sorry for today.

558
00:34:50.630 --> 00:34:53.758
Should you ever return.
I'll give you a better tour.

559
00:34:54.884 --> 00:34:56.594
-You're leaving?
-Yeah.

560
00:34:57.720 --> 00:35:00.348
I only stopped by to give you the book.

561
00:35:02.141 --> 00:35:06.187
There's actually another man outside
since my brother and his people returned.

562
00:35:06.270 --> 00:35:07.313
Oh.

563
00:35:07.396 --> 00:35:13.111
And he doesn't speak English.
so he cannot bother you the way I did.

564
00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:14.779
I wasn't bothered.

565
00:35:14.862 --> 00:35:16.322
I promise.

566
00:35:18.866 --> 00:35:21.410
I'm sure Mr. Creasy will be here soon.

567
00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:23.371
Yeah.

568
00:35:27.834 --> 00:35:28.668
Livro?

569
00:35:32.880 --> 00:35:35.842
Will you wait with me until he comes?

570
00:35:40.304 --> 00:35:42.348
Yeah-- Yeah. of course.

571
00:35:46.310 --> 00:35:48.312
[music turns ominous]

572
00:36:03.619 --> 00:36:05.621
[music intensifies]

573
00:36:21.554 --> 00:36:22.805
Shit.

574
00:36:23.598 --> 00:36:25.766
[in Portuguese]
My wallet is on the seat. You can--

575
00:36:25.850 --> 00:36:27.101
Hands on the wheel!

576
00:36:28.352 --> 00:36:30.188
We don't want your wallet.

577
00:36:30.938 --> 00:36:32.648
This is what we're looking for.

578
00:36:35.318 --> 00:36:36.736
You gave this man a ride?

579
00:36:39.155 --> 00:36:41.073
-I don't know…
-Let me be clear.

580
00:36:41.157 --> 00:36:43.868
This only ends well for you
if you have the information.

581
00:36:43.951 --> 00:36:47.788
Otherwise. you'll be another dead driver
whose phone got grabbed.

582
00:36:48.331 --> 00:36:51.125
Why don't you look again?

583
00:36:53.878 --> 00:36:54.754
[exhales sharply]

584
00:36:55.379 --> 00:36:57.798
-I drove him around days ago.
-Nothing since then?

585
00:36:57.882 --> 00:36:59.258
[gasps]

586
00:36:59.342 --> 00:37:01.677
-I drove him again.
-Was there anyone with him?

587
00:37:02.261 --> 00:37:03.971
[man clicks tongue threateningly]

588
00:37:04.055 --> 00:37:05.848
Was there anyone with him?

589
00:37:05.932 --> 00:37:07.058
A girl.

590
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:10.978
Where did you take them?

591
00:37:11.062 --> 00:37:13.439
Do you really want
to lose your life over this?

592
00:37:15.274 --> 00:37:17.860
-It was a favela.
-That's where you're going to take us.

593
00:37:19.028 --> 00:37:20.613
If we find them.

594
00:37:21.113 --> 00:37:22.698
you will be free.

595
00:37:22.782 --> 00:37:24.242
If we don't find it.

596
00:37:24.742 --> 00:37:26.118
you'll die.

597
00:37:26.619 --> 00:37:27.954
Go.

598
00:37:28.037 --> 00:37:28.955
[stick shift clacks]

599
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:32.708
[music fades]

600
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:36.587
[in English] Creasy should have been back
by now. Okay. we have a plane to meet.

601
00:37:36.671 --> 00:37:39.257
-I'm sure he's coming--
-No. he's not!

602
00:37:39.340 --> 00:37:42.301
Okay? I don't even know who to call.
He didn't tell me anything. Livro.

603
00:37:42.385 --> 00:37:45.137
-He will come.
-God. why do you keep saying that?

604
00:37:46.222 --> 00:37:49.058
-[sighs]
-Because no one would leave you behind.

605
00:38:02.238 --> 00:38:04.240
[crickets chirping]

606
00:38:13.332 --> 00:38:14.333
[engine shuts off]

607
00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:20.589
[Osmar sighs]

608
00:38:22.383 --> 00:38:25.511
-[in Portuguese] What time tomorrow?
-You will know when I do.

609
00:38:26.095 --> 00:38:28.097
[owl hooting]

610
00:38:30.558 --> 00:38:31.475
[door opens]

611
00:38:34.562 --> 00:38:35.479
[door closes]

612
00:38:36.856 --> 00:38:38.858
[dog barking distantly]

613
00:38:40.818 --> 00:38:42.820
[ominous music playing]

614
00:39:11.974 --> 00:39:13.517
[door opens]

615
00:39:14.685 --> 00:39:16.395
-[Osmar chuckles]
-[music fades]

616
00:39:16.479 --> 00:39:17.313
Mateus.

617
00:39:17.396 --> 00:39:20.191
-What are you doing up. little man?
-I thought I heard something.

618
00:39:20.274 --> 00:39:21.859
Just your old man getting ready for bed.

619
00:39:22.443 --> 00:39:23.861
Come on. we'll get you tucked in.

620
00:39:27.531 --> 00:39:29.075
-Is that good?
-Yes.

621
00:39:29.158 --> 00:39:30.826
[cell phone ringing]

622
00:39:30.910 --> 00:39:31.786
[cell phone beeps]

623
00:39:31.869 --> 00:39:32.995
Yeah.

624
00:39:34.246 --> 00:39:35.623
You're kidding.

625
00:39:36.791 --> 00:39:38.959
Tell me where you are.
and I will get to you.

626
00:39:42.254 --> 00:39:43.589
Agreed.

627
00:39:44.090 --> 00:39:45.299
Is everything okay?

628
00:39:45.383 --> 00:39:47.301
Daddy just has to go out again.

629
00:39:47.385 --> 00:39:49.762
You sleep well and we'll talk tomorrow.

630
00:39:49.845 --> 00:39:50.805
-Okay?
-Okay.

631
00:39:50.888 --> 00:39:51.931
Good night. son.

632
00:39:52.014 --> 00:39:53.641
Good night. Dad.

633
00:40:11.867 --> 00:40:13.869
[ominous music playing]

634
00:40:23.212 --> 00:40:26.215
[music crescendos. fades]

635
00:40:28.467 --> 00:40:30.469
[Portuguese rap music playing]

636
00:40:45.151 --> 00:40:46.902
[in English] <i>♪ Shake your body. baby ♪</i>

637
00:40:46.986 --> 00:40:48.737
[lyrics continue in Portuguese]

638
00:41:26.734 --> 00:41:27.985
[music fades]

639
00:41:28.305 --> 00:42:28.230
